\b The Data:\

\b0 To test this, I grabbed Environment Canada daily weather data from Calgary Int\'92l A ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://climate.weather.gc.ca/climateData/dailydata_e.html?timeframe=2&Prov=AB&StationID=2205&dlyRange=1881-10-01%7C2012-07-11&Year=1906&Month=10&cmdB1=Go&Day=1"}}{\fldrslt http://climate.weather.gc.ca/climateData/dailydata_e.html?timeframe=2&Prov=AB&StationID=2205&dlyRange=1881-10-01%7C2012-07-11&Year=1906&Month=10&cmdB1=Go&Day=1}}) for the period 1907 \'97 2012, using my sweet little web-scraper [insert link]. \
\
From my breakfast research, I couldn\'92t find any climate studies that had quantitative ways to define Chinooks, but there were a few health studies ({\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://stroke.ahajournals.org/content/33/7/1751.full"}}{\fldrslt 
\f1 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 http://stroke.ahajournals.org/content/33/7/1751.full}}
